        checkItems: ['Past tense', 'Storytelling'],
        sections: [
          { type: 'info-box', content: 'Master past tense (simple, continuous, perfect) to tell stories and recount experiences. Learn narrative structures and connecting words. Essential for sharing memories, describing events, and engaging listeners with vivid storytelling.' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Simple Past Tense Structure' },
          { type: 'text', content: '• Regular verbs: Base + -ed (walk → walked, play → played)\n• Irregular verbs: Unique forms (go → went, eat → ate, see → saw)\n• Negatives: did not + base verb | "I didn\'t go to the party."\n• Questions: Did + subject + verb? | "Did you see the movie?"\n• Time expressions: yesterday, last week, ago, in 2020, when I was young' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Common Irregular Past Forms' },
          { type: 'text', content: 'be→was/were / have→had / do→did / go→went / see→saw / eat→ate / drink→drank / write→wrote / speak→spoke / come→came / take→took / make→made / find→found / give→gave / tell→told / know→knew / think→thought / get→got / leave→left / feel→felt / become→became' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Past Continuous (was/were + -ing)' },
          { type: 'text', content: '• Used for: Actions happening at a specific time in the past\n• Structure: Subject + was/were + verb-ing\n• Examples:\n  - "I was watching TV when she called."\n  - "We were having dinner at 8 PM."\n  - "They were playing football yesterday afternoon."\n• Interrupted action: "I was reading when the power went out."\n• Two simultaneous actions: "While I was cooking, he was setting the table."' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Present Perfect (have/has + past participle)' },
          { type: 'text', content: '• Used for: Recent events with present relevance, or indefinite past\n• Structure: have/has + past participle\n• Examples:\n  - "I have finished my homework."\n  - "She has worked here for five years."\n  - "We have never been to Japan."\n  - "Have you ever tried sushi?"\n• Time expressions: recently, yet, already, for, since, ever, never' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Narrative Connectors & Linking Words' },
          { type: 'text', content: '• Once upon a time, ... | Classic story opening | "Once upon a time, there was a princess."\n• One day, ... | Event beginning | "One day, I decided to travel."\n• First, ... | Sequence start | "First, I packed my bags."\n• Then, ... | Next event | "Then, I called a taxi."\n• After that, ... | Subsequent event | "After that, I went to the airport."\n• Meanwhile, ... | Simultaneous action | "Meanwhile, my friend was waiting there."\n• While ... | During time period | "While I was traveling, I made new friends."\n• Just as ... | Precise moment | "Just as I arrived, the train left."\n• Before long, ... | Soon after | "Before long, I realized I loved traveling."\n• Eventually, ... | Final result | "Eventually, I returned home."\n• Finally, ... | Conclusion | "Finally, I had the best vacation ever."\n• In the end, ... | Ultimate outcome | "In the end, it was an unforgettable experience."\n• Looking back, ... | Reflection | "Looking back, I realize how lucky I was."\n• To my surprise, ... | Unexpected event | "To my surprise, I won a prize."\n• Unfortunately, ... | Negative turn | "Unfortunately, I lost my passport."\n• Luckily, ... | Positive resolution | "Luckily, someone helped me find it."' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Building a Complete Story' },
          { type: 'text', content: '• Setting: Where and when? | "It was a cold December evening in Paris."\n• Characters: Who? | "I was traveling with my best friend, Sarah."\n• Problem/Challenge: What happened? | "Suddenly, we realized we were lost."\n• Actions/Events: What did they do? | "We asked for directions and found a warm café."\n• Emotions/Reactions: How did they feel? | "We felt relieved and grateful for the help."\n• Resolution: How did it end? | "We found our hotel and had a wonderful night."\n• Lesson/Reflection: What did it teach? | "That experience taught me to be more prepared."' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Storytelling Dialogue Example' },
          { type: 'text', content: 'Friend: "Tell me an interesting story from your travels."\nYou: "Once upon a time, I went hiking in the mountains. First, I woke up very early and started at dawn. After about three hours, I was climbing steep rocks when suddenly, I saw an eagle flying above me. Then, I realized I had lost the trail. Luckily, I found a map and reoriented myself. While I was resting, a local man passed by and helped me. Before long, I reached the summit. The view was incredible! Eventually, I came down as the sun was setting. In the end, it was the most memorable hiking trip ever!"\nFriend: "Wow! Were you scared when you lost the trail?"\nYou: "Yes, I was quite worried. But looking back now, it makes the story even better!"' },
          { type: 'heading', level: 2, content: 'Personal Experience Story Dialogue' },
          { type: 'text', content: 'Scene: Sharing a past experience\n\n→ A: "Have you ever had an embarrassing moment?"\n← B: "Oh yes! I have many. Once, I went to a job interview and had food on my face the whole time."\n→ A: "No! What happened?"\n← B: "I was eating breakfast before the interview. I didn\'t notice I had jam on my chin. While the interviewer was talking, I was nervously trying to look professional, but they eventually told me about the stain."\n→ A: "That\'s so awkward! Did you get the job?"\n← B: "Surprisingly, I did! They said my humility and ability to laugh at myself impressed them."\n→ A: "Well, that\'s a great ending! Have you ever had something like that again?"\n← B: "Not yet, but I learned to check the mirror carefully before important meetings!"' },
        ],
